<h1>Chapter 8</h1>

<h2>8.1 Introduction</h2>

<p>
This chapter explains important statistical concepts related to the
analysis and interpretation of data. Statistical tools help summarize,
organize, and draw conclusions from collected data.
</p>

<p>
Understanding these concepts allows researchers, scientists,
and analysts to make informed decisions based on numerical evidence.
</p>

<div class="diagram">
<img src="images/ch8-diagram1.png" alt="Statistical Diagram">
<p>Figure 8.1 – Example statistical representation</p>
</div>


<h2>8.2Key Concepts</h2>

<p>
Statistical analysis often involves summarizing large datasets
into meaningful indicators such as averages, dispersion, and trends.
</p>

<h3>8.2.1 Important Measures</h3>

<ul>
<li>Mean</li>
<li>Median</li>
<li>Mode</li>
<li>Variance</li>
<li>Standard Deviation</li>
</ul>

<div class="formula">
Mean = (Σx) / n
</div>

<div class="formula">
Variance = Σ (x − μ)² / n
</div>

<div class="formula">
Standard Deviation = √Variance
</div>


<h2>8.3 Example Calculation</h2>

<div class="example">

<p>Consider the following dataset:</p>

<table>
<tr>
<th>Value</th>
<th>Frequency</th>
</tr>

<tr>
<td>10</td>
<td>2</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td>20</td>
<td>3</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td>30</td>
<td>5</td>
</tr>

</table>

<p>
Step 1: Multiply value with frequency  
</p>

<p>
Step 2: Sum all products  
</p>

<p>
Step 3: Divide by total frequency to obtain the mean
</p>

</div>



